/opt/webapp/application.war

set the log int /var/log/webapp/application-log.log

## Install Java
```
sudo yum install java-1.8.0-openjdk-devel
```
for JDK 11
```
yum install java-11-openjdk-devel
```
Verify the installtioin:
```
rpm -qa | grep 
```
## 1- System V Init
```
sudo ln -s /path/to/your-app.jar /etc/init.d/your-app
sudo service your-app start
```
## 2- Java as a Service Systemd
we create a script named your-app.service using the following example and put it in /etc/systemd/system directory:
```
[Unit]
Description=A Spring Boot application
After=syslog.target
 
[Service]
User=baeldung
ExecStart=/path/to/your-app.jar 
SuccessExitStatus=143 
 
[Install] 
WantedBy=multi-user.target
```
